= The Telephone Workers Strike

The National Telephone Union has declared a strike! Since the National Telephone Company is one of the most expolitative indsutries in Spain. Its monopoly, from which its exploitative potential grows, also violates the law. The workers, part of our union and mostly women, have independently decided to stop this injustice have declared a strike!

Since before the Republic, even the moderate Socialist leaders have vowed to reform the National Telephone Company. Right now, Senor Largo Caballero is a Minister of Labour. Most of our members say that the workers are right and now is the right time for this strike. Though some members from Cataloia argue that right now the interior issues of the CNT must take precedence over a labour dispute we can always devote our energy to resolve later.

How does the National Committee react?

