The National Committee, though reluctant at first, bends to the mass members' pleas to support our comrades. We shall express solidarity thorugh our official newspaper and gather funds for the families of the workers on strike. A la huelga, companeros!

@nostrike
on-arrival: revolutionary_dissent += 5; reformist_strength += 5; psoe_relation += 5.

Now is REALLY not the right time for this, not only because of the important divisive issues that we are yet to decide, but also because we shouldn't destabilize the same Republic that we helped bring to existance. The National Committee shall support publicly the strikers, but not too enthusiastically and we must be sure to reprimand them in private. Later there will be plenty of time to strike...when we are ready!

@aftermath_1

Regardless of our efforts, the strike was immediately declared as an illegal one and the Guardia Civil arrived to detain the workers. Despite fierce guerrila fights, 2 000 of the 7 000 unionists were arrested. Curse the Socialist betrayal!

@aftermath_2

Despite the workers' best efforts, the strike was immediately declared as an illegal one and the Guardia Civil arrived to detain the workers. Despite fierce guerrila fights, 2 000 of the 7 000 unionists were arrested. Such are the fruits of haste...
